courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students will be able to:

1. Apply the learning and teaching principles of different learning areas when designing learning activities;
2. Understand the principles and key concepts underpinning the design, implementation, and evaluation of ECE curriculum;
3. Demonstrate skills in planning and delivering developmentally appropriate learning experiences for young children;
4. Demonstrate skills in assessing the learning of young children; and

5. Develop programmes facilitating children’s smooth transition from home to school and from preschool to primary education.

courses.course_syllabus:
The course will cover topics such as:

1. Learning and teaching principles of different learning areas, such as Self and Society, Nature and Living, Physical Fitness and Health, Arts and Creativity, Early Childhood Mathematics and Language;
2. Principles and key concepts underpinning the design, implementation, and evaluation of ECE curriculum;
3. Setting age and developmentally appropriate curriculum goals and instructional objectives;
4. Organizing the curriculum in ways to meet the diverse developmental and learning needs of children;
5. Designing child-centered learning activities for children;
6. Skills in delivering quality learning experiences for young children

7. Conducting authentic assessment on children’s learning and developing portfolio to document their learning; and

8. Issues relating to smooth transition from home to school and the interface between preschool and primary school.

