courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students will be able to:

1. understand the basic principles and theories of ECE;
2. analyze the diverse social and cultural factors influencing ECE;
3. distinguish the unique features of different ECE approaches;
4. discuss contemporary ECE issues in Hong Kong; and

5. identify the professional roles of early childhood educators.

courses.course_syllabus:
The core content covers:

1. types and goals of ECE services;
2. pioneers and advocators of ECE;
3. learning theories of ECE: e.g. conditional theories, constructivism;
4. basic principles of ECE: child-centeredness, educare;
5. ECE approaches: thematic approach, inquiry-based learning, project, play-based curriculum;
6. different dimensions of professionalism in ECE;
7. socio-cultural factors influencing the ECE service provision in Hong Kong; and

8. contemporary ECE issues in Hong Kong: e.g. 15-year free education, the revised curriculum guide.

courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of the course, students are expected to:

(i) explain the concept of creativity and its role in the early years of development;
(ii) acquire abilities to design activities to enhance children’s creative expressions in various forms of arts;
(iii) gain knowledge in assessing creative arts activities and curriculum;
(iv) deepen own experience of play as an ideal form for creative expressions;
(v) analyze teacher's roles in enhancing children’s creativity

Assessment and its relation to learning outcomes:

Essays (50%) - Learning outcomes #1, 2, 3, 4

Presentation (30%) - Learning outcomes #1, 2, 4, 5

Others (classwork) (20%) - Learning outcomes #1, 4, 5

Upon completion of the course, participants should be able to:

1. understand the characteristics, theories and practices of play;
2. design and implement play activities to foster young children’s language, cognitive, social, emotional, and physical development;
3. develop resources for play activities;
4. assess children's learning and development in play.

After the course, participants will be able to:
1. understand recent school management reforms in Hong Kong and their impacts on preschools and kindergartens;
2. examine various roles of early childhood teachers in relation to school reforms and school-based management;
3. have a basic understanding of various school management concepts and their application in daily operation of early childhood education institutions;
4. identify areas for school improvement based on information gathered from annual school self-evaluation and external school review;
5. reflect critically on individual competency, school practices and capacity for change by linking theories and practices in the context of early childhood education.

After the course, students will be able to:
1. understand parents’ roles in young children education;
2. identify socio-economic factors related to parental involvement in young children’s education
3. demonstrate competency in enhancing home school communication for young children’s learning, such as academic, socio-emotional development;
4. demonstrate competency in planning parental involvement in school activities;
5. demonstrate competence in strengthening collaboration with parents and community, including promoting their understanding on quality ECE and contribute in implementing early children curriculum .

By the end of the course, students will be able to:

1. demonstrate competence and broad understanding of the professional standards and basic legal knowledge for teachers in Hong Kong;
2. identify moral dilemmas facing teachers and make responsible decisions by considering different ethical perspectives, and finding the best possible way forward for all stakeholders;
3. act conscientiously with regard to the professional standards and the law, and collaborate ethically and competently in multi-disciplinary and multi-cultural teams; and
4. develop a commitment to the teaching profession and reflect on the professional standards in individual practices.

The intended Learning Outcomes of TP are that students will:

(1) demonstrate teaching competence ;
(2) integrate and apply pedagogical content knowledge in practice;
(3) apply concepts of reflective practice to authentic classroom and

(4) develop appropriate attitudes and values of a qualified teacher.
